snippet: The man arrested on homicide charges after three people were shot to death at a township meeting in Pennsylvania had faced eviction from his dilapidated property.
abstract: Rockne Warren Newell is arrested on homicide charges after three people were shot to death at township meeting in eastern Pennsylvania; incident appears to be linked to Newell's impending eviction from his dilapidated property.

byline.contributor: Jennifer Preston contributed reporting, and Sheelagh McNeill contributed research.

lead_paragraph: The man arrested on homicide charges after three people were shot to death at a township meeting in Pennsylvania had faced eviction from his dilapidated property.

headline.main: Gunfire at Board Meeting Traced to Eviction Dispute
headline.print_headline: Gunfire at Board Meeting Traced to Eviction Dispute
